lead_paragraph: We have received from the Publishers during the last week, a number of books of which we have been unable, as yet, to take proper notice. The Book press, now-a-day, is suite as active and quite as productive as the Newspaper press. There never has been a time before in the history of the world, when so many volumes were issued, and at so cheap a rate.
